SIMPLE: worst
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Worst
<hw>Worst</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>, <pos>superl.</pos> of
<er>Bad</er>. <ety>[OE. <ets>werst</ets>, <ets>worste</ets>,
<ets>wurste</ets>, AS. <ets>wyrst</ets>, <ets>wierst</ets>,
<ets>wierrest</ets>. See <er>Worse</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Bad,
evil, or pernicious, in the highest degree, whether in a physical or
moral sense. See <er>Worse</er>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Heard so oft in
<xex>worst</xex> extremes.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q> I have a wife, the <qex>worst</qex> that may be.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If thou hadst not been born the <qex>worst</qex> of men,⟦br⟧
Thou hadst been a knave and flatterer.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worst</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Worst
<hw>Worst</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is most bad or evil; the
most severe, pernicious, calamitous, or wicked state or
degree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>worst</qex> is not⟦br⟧
So long as we can say, This is the <qex>worst</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is always sure of finding diversion when the <qex>worst</qex>
comes to the <qex>worst</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worst</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Worst
<hw>Worst</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Worsted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Worsting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See <er>Worse</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos> & <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>To gain advantage over, in contest
or competition; to get the better of; to defeat; to overthrow; to
discomfit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The . . . Philistines were <qex>worsted</qex> by the captivated
ark.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worst</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Worst
<hw>Worst</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To grow worse; to
deteriorate.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Every face . . .
<xex>worsting</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Jane Austen.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Worsted</ent>⟦br⟧
